Option 1: The "Resume" (Best first step)
Just run your ipa-replica-install command again exactly as you did before.
The installer will detect the existing LDAP data and the running CA.
Because the indexing is finished, it will fly through the "configuring certificate server" step that failed last time.
Option 2: The "Force" Resume (If Option 1 tells you to uninstall)
If the installer refuses to run because it sees a failed state, you can often "trick" it into continuing by telling it the server is configured:
Create the missing state file:
bash
touch /var/lib/ipa/sysrestore/sysrestore.state
Use code with caution.

Run the install again.
Important: Verify the CA one last time
Before you run the installer, make sure that curl command actually returns the "Running" XML:
bash
curl -sk https://pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local
